# Description
This program determines the minimum number of swaps needed so that all couples sit together. It uses a greedy strategy by processing seats in pairs and immediately swapping in the correct partner when necessary. 
A position array is maintained to allow constant-time lookup of any person’s location. The algorithm runs in O(n) time and uses O(n) space.

